title: Alphabet Earnings Preview: Fiscal Q2 2025
text: Coming into the Q2 2025 earnings today, Alphabet Inc.'s total revenue expectations of $94 billion for the quarter have remained stable since February. Operating profit and EPS have been grinding higher recently, due to the continued expected strength of the cloud business. Consensus is estimating Q2 Cloud revenue of $13.1 billion, flat since February 2025.

title: Alphabet Earnings Preview: Google's Very Own Version Of Creative Destruction
text: Alphabet reports their Q2 '25 financial results after the closing bell on Wednesday night, July 23rd, 2025. Analyst consensus is expecting $2.18 in earnings per share on $93.9-94 billion in revenue and $31.1 billion in revenue for expected y-o-y growth of 15%, 11%, and 13%, respectively. Advertising is still 74% of total GOOGL revenue as of the March '25 quarter, but the fact is that metric has been slowly declining from the low 80% range in 2022.

title: Are You Smart Than a Teenager? Google A.I.
text: Alphabet's (GOOGL) DeepMind beat many high schoolers in the International Mathematical Olympiad, solving a majority of top-level math questions posed to students. Jenny Horne gives more insight into the story and offers insight into what this means for the progress on A.I.

title: GOOGL Earnings: The Cheapest of the Magnificent 7
text: Alphabet ( GOOGL ) heads into its second-quarter earnings report on July 23 with something to prove. While the stock is flat year-to-date, lagging significantly behind Nvidia ( NVDA ), Microsoft ( MSFT ) and Meta Platforms ( META ), it is in line with the performance of Amazon ( AMZN ) and much better than Tesla ( TSLA ) and Apple ( AAPL ).

title: As Alphabet's earnings approach, investors will get a first read on this hot AI trend
text: Cloud results from Alphabet, Amazon and Microsoft should show benefits from the explosive rise of AI agents.

title: Alphabet: Mispriced And Built To Compound
text: Alphabet operates a vast suite of interconnected businesses, each feeding into an ecosystem with extreme levels of user lock-in, creating massive monetization potential. Google continues to be valued through the narrow lens of Search which is viewed as being in secular decline and is ignoring its other strong businesses. My sum-of-the-parts valuation suggests a fair value of $217/share which suggests at least 14% upside. This excludes the potential of Waymo.

title: Google Wants to Recruit News Outlets for AI Licensing Project
text: Google reportedly wants to recruit news companies for an AI-related licensing project. The tech giant hopes to launch a pilot project with around 20 national news organizations, Bloomberg News reported Tuesday (July 22), citing sources familiar with the matter.
